sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(annotation_id) AS num_annotations
FROM annotations
GROUP BY user_id;

SELECT MIN(depth_from) AS min_depth, MAX(depth_to) AS max_depth
FROM soil_layers
WHERE project_id = (SELECT project_id FROM projects WHERE project_name = '<Project Name>');

external_knowledge:
- 'flagged with issues' refers to soil layers having annotations of type 'Warning';
- 'typical depth' in this context means the average depth from which these issue-flagged layers start;
- We are examining projects in which such layers are present and summarizing their typical depths.

